Package: CountMissingByGroup
Type: Package
Title: Count missing values for all columns by group
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person('Shengyu','Zuo',email='zuoshengyu1127@gmail.com',role = c('aut','cre'))
Description: Given a data frame `data` and a column `group`, `count_all_missing_by_group()` creates a new data frame with one row per level of `group`.
    The first column of the output data frame contains the levels of `group`, and the rest of the columns contain the number of missing values for all columns in `data` except `group`.  
